SIMPLE: mutable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mutable
<hw>Mu"ta*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mutabilis</ets>, fr. <ets>mutare</ets> to change. See
<er>Move</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of alteration; subject to
change; changeable in form, qualities, or nature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Things of the most accidental and <qex>mutable</qex> nature.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Changeable; inconstant; unsettled; unstable;
fickle.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Most <xex>mutable</xex> wishes.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Byron.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Changeable; alterable; unstable; unsteady;
unsettled; wavering; inconstant; variable; fickle.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mutableness</ent>⟦br⟧
